Vietnam Stock Movers: Phu Nhuan Jewelry, Vietnam Dairy Products

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-22T05:09:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/vietnam-stock-movers-phu-nhuan-jewelry-vietnam-dairy-products.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Vietnam  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 11 a.m. local-time close.  The VN Index, the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, dropped 0.7 percent to 464.8.       Vietnam Dairy Products Joint-Stock Co. (VNM VN), rose 0.5
percent to 92,500 dong, the highest level since March 8. The
company won approval from the State Securities Commission to
raise its foreign ownership ratio to 49 percent from 46 percent,
it said in a statement on the exchange’s website. Vinamilk, as
it’s also known, also got permission to cancel its Singapore
listing plan, according to the statement.       Phu Nhuan Jewelry Joint-Stock Co. (PNJ VN), the only
jewelry manufacturer on the exchange, sank 4.8 percent to 27,900
dong, the lowest level since May 22, 2009.  Vietnam’s government must quickly come up with measures to
restrict the use of dollars and gold in trading and as payment
tools, Ha Van Hien, chairman of the National Assembly’s
Committee for Economic Affairs, said in a speech in  Hanoi 
yesterday.  To contact the Bloomberg News Staff on this story:
Nguyen Kieu Giang in Hanoi at 
